      },
      "source": [
        "#### TF-IDF\n",
        "$$\\text{tf-idf}(t,d) = \\text{tf}_{t,d}\\cdot \\text{idf}_t$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- tf $\\rightarrow$ la frecuencia del término:\n",
        "$$ \\text{tf}_{t,d} = \\begin{cases} 1 + \\log_{10} \\text{count}(t,d) & \\text{si } \\text{count}(t,d) > 0 \\\\ 0 & \\text{en otro caso} \\end{cases} $$\n",
        "- idf $\\rightarrow$  la frecuencia inversa del documento:\n",
        "$$ \\text{idf}_t = \\log_{10} \\left( \\frac{N}{\\text{df}_t} \\right) $$\n",
        "donde N es el número total de documentos en la colección, y $\\text{df}_t$ es el número de documentos en los que aparece el término $t$. Cuantos menos documentos aparezcan, mayor será este peso. Los términos que ocurren en solo unos pocos documentos son útiles para discriminar\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "- Ya está normalizado\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "z1JSHUOXpLS-",
        "outputId": "c9847e4b-34d2-4d8d-f0b7-7d324bbb6ce1"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "--- CARGANDO MATRICES TF-IDF DESDE DRIVE ---\n",
            "Dimensiones X_train_tfidf: (375713, 10000)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import scipy.sparse\n",
        "\n",
        "# Cambiamos la extensión a .npz (el formato para matrices dispersas)\n",
        "ruta_train_tfidf = os.path.join(drive_dir, 'X_train_tfidf.npz')\n",
        "ruta_test_tfidf = os.path.join(drive_dir, 'X_test_tfidf.npz')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Comprobamos si los archivos ya existen\n",
        "if (os.path.exists(ruta_train_tfidf) and os.path.exists(ruta_test_tfidf)):\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"--- CARGANDO MATRICES TF-IDF DESDE DRIVE ---\")\n",
        "    # Usamos load_npz en lugar de np.load\n",
        "    X_train_tfidf = scipy.sparse.load_npz(ruta_train_tfidf)\n",
        "    X_test_tfidf = scipy.sparse.load_npz(ruta_test_tfidf)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"Dimensiones X_train_tfidf: {X_train_tfidf.shape}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    t_emb_tfidf = 1.35 #EDITADAS POR MÍ\n",
        "    mem_emb_tfidf = 28119.14\n",
        "\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"--- ENTRENANDO TF-IDF ---\")\n",
        "    t0_emb = time()\n",
        "    mem0_emb = get_memory()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Inicializamos y entrenamos el vectorizador\n",
        "    tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=10000, ngram_range=(1, 2))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Quitamos el .toarray() para mantener la matriz comprimida\n",
        "    X_train_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(X_train_clean)\n",
        "    X_test_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.transform(X_test_clean)\n",
        "\n",
        "    t_emb_tfidf = round((time() - t0_emb)/60, 2)\n",
        "    mem_emb_tfidf = round(get_memory() - mem0_emb, 2)\n",
        "    print(f\"TF-IDF listo en {t_emb_tfidf} minutos.\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Memoria: {mem_emb_tfidf}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Dimensiones X_train_tfidf: {X_train_tfidf.shape}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Usamos save_npz en lugar de np.save\n",
        "    scipy.sparse.save_npz(ruta_train_tfidf, X_train_tfidf)\n",
        "    scipy.sparse.save_npz(ruta_test_tfidf, X_test_tfidf)"
      ]
